⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Snowball
node AFM · AFM · ⟦Snowball:AFM:4f677d⟧

WHO   — Snowball — the exiled rival
WHAT  — The idealist rival: he organises and plans, then is chased off the farm by Napoleon's dogs and blamed for everything after.
WHERE — AFM · ANIMAL FARM  Framework inputs: Animal Farm (George Orwell, 1945)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because revolutions need a scapegoat — the exiled ‘traitor’ onto whom every failure is projected.
HOW   — By eloquence, committees, and the windmill scheme — until the dogs run him off and propaganda makes him the enemy.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I planned the windmill and they ran me off with dogs — and after that, every broken thing on the farm was my fault by decree.

